      "amount": "1 cup"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in the pressure cooker over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped onion and cook until it is translucent.",
    "Add the minced garlic and cook for 1 minute.",
    "Add the halved baby plum tomatoes, mustard, cumin, salt, and black pepper, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the chicken broth and bring the mixture to a boil.",
    "Close the lid of the pressure cooker and cook for 10 minutes.",
    "Let the pressure release naturally, then open the lid and check the seasoning.",
    "Serve the stew hot, garnished with chopped fresh herbs if desired."
  ],
